# Macrosofty netinstall kickstart for @@EDITION@@.
#
# This file is the source of truth for what a Macrosofty netinstall does.
# The CI workflow at .github/workflows/iso-netinstall.yml takes this file,
# substitutes @@EDITION@@ with the edition name, and uses mkksiso to embed
# the result into Fedora 43's standard netinstall ISO. The output is a
# Macrosofty-branded netinstall ISO that pulls our OCI image from GHCR
# at install time.
#
# Anaconda screens not specified here get presented to the user
# interactively in the graphical installer — partitioning, user creation,
# network setup, root password. That's the point of a netinstall: the
# user keeps control of those choices, and only the OS payload is
# pre-configured.

# --- Run mode --------------------------------------------------------------
# `graphical` = use Anaconda's GTK graphical installer. The user sees
# the standard Fedora installer screens with our payload pre-wired.
graphical

# --- Locale defaults (user can override interactively) ---------------------
keyboard --xlayouts='us'
lang en_US.UTF-8
timezone Africa/Johannesburg --utc

# --- Payload --------------------------------------------------------------
# This is the magic line. Anaconda fetches the OCI image from GHCR at
# install time and `bootc install`s it onto the partitioned disk.
# --transport=registry means "treat the URL as a container registry ref"
# (vs. file:// or oci-archive). --no-signature-verification because we
# haven't wired the cosign signature check into Anaconda's payload yet —
# v0.2 work, alongside the netinstall hardening.
ostreecontainer \
    --url=ghcr.io/macrosofty/@@EDITION@@:latest \
    --transport=registry \
    --no-signature-verification

# --- Post-install ---------------------------------------------------------
# Reboot when finished so the user lands on the freshly installed system
# rather than the installer media.
reboot

# Run the firstboot wizard on first login (KDE Plasma's, plus our
# Macrosofty firstboot Brewfile that pulls the edition's Flatpaks).
firstboot --enable
